@NODE Introduction "Introduction"
This little Amigaguide file will help you check the cost of your phonebill
before it arrives.

So, if you've ever worred about the cost or even what your parents are
going to do to you ;) this guide is for you.

** If you find this guide usefull and you feel I should be rewarded for   
** finding this number then please, give my BBS a ring - you can find the 
** number in the contacts section.                                        

@ENDNODE

@NODE Instructions "Step By Step Instructions... "
What should You Have ..

 A telephone       - Emmmm, enough said ;)
 A phonebill       - Anyone, doesn't matter how old.
 This Guide        - Go's without saying. 




Step 1.
-------
Pick up the phone and dial 0800 854608 -  yes it's a free number!




Step 2.
-------
After a few sections you should be greated 

   "Hello, wellcome to BT's Call My Bill Service"

You will then be prompted to press the star button twice, if you don't
you will be connected to a operator :(




Step 3.
-------
Once you have pressed the star button twice, you will hear a ringing tone,
don't worry, it always happens!

Now, after the voice prompt, enter your full phone number.

Eg, Don't forget the STD code -    01424 123456
                                   ^^^^^


                                   
Step 4.
-------
Now you must enter the first 8 numbers of your BT customer number, this
can be found in the top right hand corner of your phonebill,
normally this will be will be a mixture of numbers and letters.

Eg,   Customer Account Number - 12345678 ABC DEF 123 
                                ^^^^^^^^
                                    |
You only need the first 8 ----------+




Step 5.
-------
You will then be told how much your bill is.....



